data.description: Welcome to this lovely 1900s colonial situated at the end of Gardners Neck Road/Bay Point. Enjoy amazing sunsets transitioning into an illuminated skyline, with Lee's River and the Braga Bridge in your backyard! This property's views are absolutely breathtaking. The home features nearly 3,500 sq. feet of space, sits on 3/4 of an acre of land, and comes with an additional barn loft and 2 car garage. Featuring three floors of above grade living space, 1488 Gardners Neck is ready to be transformed into the envy of Bay Point. The current layout includes a large open concept kitchen and dining area with views of the river, as well as a large double parlor living room with original hardwood floors. The second floor features the master bedroom with a rooftop deck, continuing to capitalize on the incredible views. The Cove Club and Swansea/Cole Marina are just seconds down the street. This is the perfect oasis for those who love the water.
